      "full_name": "Ivanchikhin Mikhail Alekseevich",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Mikhail Ivanchikhin is the Director of JSC MNII Agat (a.k.a. Moscow Research Institute Agat). JSC MNII Agat is a Russian military-industrial state enterprise that develops and produces radar transceivers for guided missiles deployed by the Russian Armed Forces, including the “9B-1103M-350 active radar homing head” used in Russian air-to-air and surface-to-air missiles. Moreover, JSC MNII Agat is part of the Almaz-Antey concern, a Russian state-owned arms manufacturer that develops anti-aircraft defence and cruise missile systems for the Russian military.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}